//
// File: zannastudio/src/ui/scene_editor_3d.zia
// Purpose: Visual hierarchy, transform/light/material/gameplay-data inspector,
//          additive importer, and shaded/wireframe VSCN viewport.
// Key invariants:
//   - The live SceneGraph is serialized back to Document.content after every
//     accepted edit; a failed serialization rolls the graph back.
//   - One complete gizmo drag creates one local-transform history snapshot.
//   - Compact windows show viewport or inspector at full width, never two slivers.
//   - Compact wrapped toolbars reserve every row so actions remain reachable.
//   - VSCN parsing and serialization use unique bounded staging files because
//     the runtime deliberately exposes file-oriented asset APIs.
//   - Hierarchy traversal and preview work are capped for hostile assets.
//   - Group inspector, reparent, and selection commands are transactional;
//     hierarchy cycles are rejected before mutation and inspector inputs never
//     inherit viewport shortcuts.
//   - Reparenting preserves the complete world transform by default and rejects
//     singular or shear-producing conversions without partial hierarchy edits.
//   - Sibling ordering moves only contiguous direct-sibling selections and
//     preserves their internal order, identity selection, and exact history.
//   - The hierarchy is a retained expandable TreeView; collapse state survives
//     refresh, selected data identifies rows, and row drops are transactional.
//   - Visibility presents a native mixed state for node groups and resolves the
//     complete selection through one rollback-safe canonical transaction.
//   - Material groups expose truthful mixed values; resolved sparse fields and
//     maps stage clone-safe assignments before one canonical transaction.
//   - Light components are reconstructed independently across all seven
//     runtime kinds and assigned through one rollback-safe VSCN transaction.
//   - Typed node metadata commits through canonical VSCN history and retains
//     exact scalar kinds, including explicit null and integral-looking floats.
//   - Project components add only missing typed node metadata across a
//     selection, aborting atomically on every type conflict.
//   - Project schema authoring has independent conflict-safe file history and
//     never changes canonical VSCN content, revision, history, or dirty state.
//   - Hierarchy Find keeps all bounded rows visible, wraps deterministically,
//     reveals nested matches, and never changes VSCN history or camera state.
//   - World-space groups execute in hierarchy preorder so selected descendants
//     never inherit an already-requested ancestor delta a second time.
//   - Move/Scale plane gestures solve both projected axes together, reject
//     edge-on planes, and commit or restore the selected group as one unit.
//   - Scale clamps only manipulated axes, preserving untouched imported values.
//   - Rotate gestures use projected rings and wrap-safe angular motion rather
//     than treating rotation as translation along an axis line.
//   - Shaded and wireframe meshes render through one windowless Canvas3D whose
//     orthographic camera exactly matches retained marker and gizmo projection.
//   - Viewport selection ray-tests visible mesh bounds before bounded node
//     markers; auxiliary-drag pan/orbit changes workspace camera state only.
// Ownership/Lifetime:
//   - Main owns one controller; WorkbenchShell owns its persistent host widgets.
//   - Staging files are deleted before every load/commit operation returns.
// Links: zannastudio/src/core/document.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_clipboard.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_authoring_controller.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_palette.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_schema.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_hierarchy_search.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_hierarchy_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_light_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_light_inspector_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_material_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_material_inspector_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_metadata_inspector_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_transform_3d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/probes/scene_rotation_ring_probe.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/probes/scene_scale_plane_probe.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/probes/scene_material_batch_probe.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/probes/scene_shaded_viewport_probe.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/probes/scene_viewport_picking_probe.zia,
//        docs/graphics3d-guide.md,
//        docs/adr/0156-listbox-selected-row-data.md,
//        docs/adr/0159-typed-scenenode-metadata-and-vscn-v6.md,
//        docs/adr/0160-project-scene-component-schemas.md,
//        docs/adr/0161-stable-scenenode-sibling-reordering.md,
//        docs/adr/0162-exact-preserve-world-scenenode-reparenting.md,
//        docs/adr/0163-stable-multiselect-and-row-aware-treeview-editing.md,
//        docs/adr/0165-scrollview-descendant-reveal.md,
//        docs/adr/0166-exact-scenenode-world-matrix-assignment.md,
//        docs/adr/0167-spinner-mixed-value-state.md,
//        docs/adr/0168-windowless-canvas3d-rendering.md,
//        docs/adr/0169-super-modifier-keys-and-studio-viewport-picking.md,
//        docs/adr/0172-public-scenenode-light-authoring-and-studio-light-inspector.md
//
//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

module scene_editor_3d;

// ============================================================================
// MODULE: scene_editor_3d
// PURPOSE: Present one VSCN document as a responsive hierarchy, shaded or
//          wireframe viewport, transform toolbar, and numeric inspector.
//
// WHERE-THIS-FITS: Main pumps this controller only for the active 3D scene.
//          SceneGraph is transient; Document.content remains the canonical
//          save, session, and recovery payload.
//
// TEACHING-NOTE: A drag mutates the live node for visual feedback but
//          serializes once on release. Escape restores copied scalar origins,
//          so cancelation never requires a partial document rewrite.
// ============================================================================

